Key Match Events: England collapsed to 105-5 in the 15th over, leaving them behind the required rate.
Ireland secured a five-run win on the Duckworth-Lewis-Stern method when the match was called off soon after.
England inflicted a collapse of 9-54 to dismiss Ireland in the final over.
Post-Match Reflections: England's performance was below-par with both bat and ball.
The result leaves them likely needing to beat Australia, New Zealand and Sri Lanka in their remaining games to go through.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The timing of the rain was unfortunate – one more ball and a Moeen six would have taken his side ahead of the score required.
England’s tactics with the bat were curious.
The Black Caps top the group on three points, with Sri Lanka, England, Ireland and Australia all a point behind.
Others: The match was called off due to rain.
The encounter against Australia, who lost to New Zealand in their opener before beating Sri Lanka, is effectively a knockout game.
